      <p><a href="ch64s04.html#MonstersDr-Dw207">Driders</a> speak Elven, Common, and Undercommon.<a href="img/MonstersDr-Dw.Drider.jpg" target="_blank"><span class="inlinemediaobject"><img src="thumb/MonstersDr-Dw.Drider.jpg" align="right"/></span></a></p>
      <div class="sect4" lang="en">
        <div class="titlepage">
          <div>
            <div>
              <h5 class="title"><a name="id1958223"/>Combat</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
          <div class="keyword">monsterinfo</div>
        </div>
        <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersDr-Dw208"/>
        <p><a href="ch64s04.html#MonstersDr-Dw207">Driders</a> seldom pass up an opportunity to attack other creatures, especially from ambush. They usually begin with a spell assault and often levitate out of the enemy's reach.</p>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id1958255"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersDr-Dw209"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Poison (Ex):</strong></span> Injury, Fortitude DC 16, initial and secondary damage 1d6 Str. The save DC is Constitution based.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id1958285"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersDr-Dw210"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Spell-Like Abilities:</strong></span> 1/day-<span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch45.html#SpellsD-E2">dancing lights</a></em></span> (DC 13), <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch44.html#SpellsC19">clairaudience/clairvoyance</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch45.html#SpellsD-E3">darkness</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch45.html#SpellsD-E21">detect good</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch45.html#SpellsD-E22">detect law</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch45.html#SpellsD-E23">detect magic</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch45.html#SpellsD-E44">dispel magic</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch46.html#SpellsF-G3">faerie fire</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch47.html#SpellsH-L66">levitate</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch50.html#SpellsS74">suggestion</a></em></span> (DC 16). Caster level 6th. The save DCs are Charisma-based.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id1958422"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersDr-Dw211"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Spells:</strong></span> <a href="ch64s04.html#MonstersDr-Dw207">Driders</a> cast spells as 6th-level clerics, wizards, or sorcerers. <a href="ch64s04.html#MonstersDr-Dw207">Drider</a> clerics can choose from the following domains: Chaos, Destruction, Evil, and Trickery. The typical spells prepared shown here are for a <a href="ch64s04.html#MonstersDr-Dw207">drider</a> sorcerer.</p>
          <p><span class="emphasis"><em>Typical Sorcerer Spells Known</em></span> (6/7/6/4, base save DC 13 + spell level): 0-<span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch45.html#SpellsD-E6">daze</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch45.html#SpellsD-E23">detect magic</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch46.html#SpellsF-G40">ghost sound</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch48.html#SpellsM-O3">mage hand</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch49.html#SpellsP-R51">ray of frost</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch49.html#SpellsP-R52">read magic</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch49.html#SpellsP-R69">resistance</a></em></span>; 1st-<span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch48.html#SpellsM-O2">mage armor</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch48.html#SpellsM-O18">magic missile</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch49.html#SpellsP-R49">ray of enfeeblement</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch50.html#SpellsS38">silent image</a></em></span>; 2nd- <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch47.html#SpellsH-L52">invisibility</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch51.html#SpellsT-Z49">web</a></em></span>; 3rd-<span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch47.html#SpellsH-L68">lightning bolt</a></em></span>.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id1958707"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersDr-Dw212"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Skills:</strong></span> A <a href="ch64s04.html#MonstersDr-Dw207">drider</a> has a +4 racial bonus on <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills179">Hide</a> and <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills211">Move Silently</a> checks. It has a +8 racial bonus on <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills71">Climb</a> checks and can always choose to take 10 on a <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills71">Climb</a> check, even if rushed or threatened.</p>
